                    "body": "more on class coding standard-related problems",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nataniel",
                        "name": "nataniel",
                        "displayName": "Artur Jedlinski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-28T03:50:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-28T03:50:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17024",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shreef",
                        "name": "shreef",
                        "displayName": "Ahmed Shreef",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "hay Artur,\nthank you for helping us get it bettter =) . yea, maybe we need to do some refactoring.\n\nthe flexible params were experimental, we wanted to see if this will be helping the users or what?, but there were no one complaining about this, so we kept it to see what will happen when Zend_Currency goes core.\n\n{quote}\n1) Static vars should be used to keep track of long \/ short \/ symbol already retrieved from Zend_Locale_Data::getContent(). This will tune the performance up without need of using cache.\n{quote}\n\nI don't know, if we will save this data in static vars, I think it's better happen in Zend_Locale_Data .\n\nwhat do you think?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shreef",
                        "name": "shreef",
                        "displayName": "Ahmed Shreef",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-30T05:38:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-30T05:38:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17025",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nataniel",
                        "name": "nataniel",
                        "displayName": "Artur Jedlinski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}I don't know, if we will save this data in static vars, I think it's better happen in Zend_Locale_Data{quote}\nYou are totally right, I didn't notice the Zend_Locale_Data actually has its current cache, sorry.\n\nOne more comment about the class:\n{code}$names = Zend_Locale_Data::getContent($this->_locale, 'currencynames', substr($this->_locale, strpos($this->_locale, '_') + 1) );{code}\nIt seems the 3rd argument (region) is not used in getContent for 'currencynames' path.\n\nI don't really like the way the constructor is built. For example there's no need to get full name, symbol, format from Zend_Locale_data unless it's really needed - I'd rather see it in methods which uses them. Since there are no such methods (another issue I've posted), there's no easy way to refactor that.\n\nSorry for being harsh Ahmed, I'm just integrating the Zend_Currency with my project and that kind of real-life use case brings a lot of problems with the class. Thanks for creating it anyway :-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nataniel",
                        "name": "nataniel",
                        "displayName": "Artur Jedlinski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-30T05:57:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-30T05:57:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17083",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The API has been completly reworked which includes this issue.\n\nPlease review and test SVN 6597 or later and give us response.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
